-long-de.toem.impulse.samples.ISamples.getRateUnits()=<b>public long getRateUnits()</b><br/>Distance between 2 samples as a multiple of its domain base (e.g. domain base=1ms; units = 100; -> domain value = 100ms).<br/><b>Class: </b><a href='https://toem.de/images/toem/impulse/javadoc3.0/de/toem/impulse/samples/ISamples.html#getRateUnits-'>de.toem.impulse.samples.ISamples</a><br/><b>Parameters:</b><ul></ul><br/><b>Returns: </b>
-int-de.toem.impulse.samples.ISamples.getRelease()=<b>public int getRelease()</b><br/>Returns the release (incremented with every extension/change of sample information) Result value shall never become less than in an earlier<br/> version and is always between 0 and MAX. ??release == 0: no inital content released ??release >= 0 < MAX: volatile ??release == MAX:<br/> non-volatile<br/><b>Class: </b><a href='https://toem.de/images/toem/impulse/javadoc3.0/de/toem/impulse/samples/ISamples.html#getRelease-'>de.toem.impulse.samples.ISamples</a><br/><b>Parameters:</b><ul></ul><br/><b>Returns: </b>
-boolean-de.toem.impulse.samples.ISamples.isVolatile()=<b>public boolean isVolatile()</b><br/>Returns true if the content can extend/change. With every change the release value is incremented. Flag may change from true to false, but<br/> never back.<br/><b>Class: </b><a href='https://toem.de/images/toem/impulse/javadoc3.0/de/toem/impulse/samples/ISamples.html#isVolatile-'>de.toem.impulse.samples.ISamples</a><br/><b>Parameters:</b><ul></ul><br/><b>Returns: </b>
-boolean-de.toem.impulse.samples.ISamples.isMonotonous()=<b>public boolean isMonotonous()</b><br/>A monotonous changes only adds new sample/legend information. Flag never changes.<br/><b>Class: </b><a href='https://toem.de/images/toem/impulse/javadoc3.0/de/toem/impulse/samples/ISamples.html#isMonotonous-'>de.toem.impulse.samples.ISamples</a><br/><b>Parameters:</b><ul></ul><br/><b>Returns: </b>
-boolean-de.toem.impulse.samples.ISamples.isReleased()=<b>public boolean isReleased()</b><br/>Returns true if an intial content is released. Flag may change from false to true, but never back.<br/><b>Class: </b><a href='https://toem.de/images/toem/impulse/javadoc3.0/de/toem/impulse/samples/ISamples.html#isReleased-'>de.toem.impulse.samples.ISamples</a><br/><b>Parameters:</b><ul></ul><br/><b>Returns: </b>
-boolean-de.toem.impulse.samples.ISamples.hasTag()=<b>public boolean hasTag()</b><br/>Returns true if at least 1 sample is tagged.If true, impulse will use tag color (usually red) to paint the sample. Meaning of 'tagged is<br/> use-case depended.<br/><b>Class: </b><a href='https://toem.de/images/toem/impulse/javadoc3.0/de/toem/impulse/samples/ISamples.html#hasTag-'>de.toem.impulse.samples.ISamples</a><br/><b>Parameters:</b><ul></ul><br/><b>Returns: </b>
